## 📝 Project Report

**Platforms Chosen:** GitHub, LinkedIn, and Kaggle.

For my digital portfolio, I established a professional presence on **GitHub**, **LinkedIn**, and **Kaggle**. I selected these specific platforms because they represent the three pillars of a modern developer’s identity: version control, professional networking, and data science proficiency. 

I use **GitHub** as a central repository for my academic code and open-source contributions. My **LinkedIn** profile serves as a professional bridge to connect with VIT alumni and industry experts, ensuring I stay updated on internship trends. Lastly, I chose **Kaggle** to explore real-world datasets, which aligns with my interest in AI and Machine Learning.

Over the next four years, I plan to use these platforms as a living record of my growth. I will push regular code commits to GitHub to maintain a verifiable "contribution streak," update LinkedIn with my certifications and project milestones, and use Kaggle to build a competitive edge in data science. Consistently maintaining these profiles will ensure that by the time I graduate in 2029, I have a robust digital footprint that demonstrates my technical evolution to potential employers at top-tier tech companies.

